description: {"blocks":[{"key":"f126j","text":"A protoplast is a living plant, fungal, or bacterial cell with the cell wall removed. Protoplasts offer a simplified system for studies of gene expression compared to more complex whole-plant systems and are promising for the interrogation of cellular physiology, metabolism and responses to stimuli. Performing live imaging of protoplast experiments in a time-course experiment provides more information about how these cellular processes progress over time. Protoplast time-course live imaging studies have previously explored intracellular auxin localization [1], auxinâ€™s effect on gene expression [2], the cellular localization of a mobile transcription factor, and its dynamic response to chemical endomembrane system inhibitors [3], cell wall regeneration [4], and cell division and micro-callus formation [5]. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"edho4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"138qc","text":"Though time-course live imaging of protoplasts is a useful tool, it is also a skill that can be difficult to acquire. Practice and troubleshooting of various protoplast isolation, transfection, and immobilization protocols can be time-consuming and may deter many from performing experiments with protoplasts. This protocol combines protoplast isolation, transfection, and immobilization methods to form a cohesive protoplast time-course live imaging protocol with notes and modifications from our troubleshooting. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fq1bv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4jois","text":"This protocol was developed for time-course live imaging of maize and sorghum protoplasts. The isolation and transfection steps are based on methods published in Meng et al. 2020 with a few modifications. First, 50mM MES was added to the PEG-calcium transfection solution to buffer the transfection solution at pH 5.7 and increase protoplast transfection efficiency . Second, 1% bovine serum albumin(BSA) was added to the incubation solution based on Ohshima et al. 1989  to increase protoplast viability after overnight incubation. Third, 50ug/mL ampicillin is added to the incubation solution to decrease bacterial growth overnight [8]. The alginate immobilization steps were adapted from Middleton et al. 2018 and Dovzhenko et al. 1998. steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"dc4r5","text":"Fill a glass petri dish with the filter sterilized enzyme solution, and set aside.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"24hbo","text":"Harvest 10-14 day old seedlings and submerge in 5% bleach 1% Tween solution for 1min., remove and rinse seedlings thoroughly in autoclaved tap water 6x. Pat seedlings dry with autoclaved Kimwipes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"28d81","text":"Cut green leaf tissue from seedlings into ~1mm strips with a fresh razor blade and immediately transfer to glass petri dish pre-filled with filter sterilized enzyme solution.     ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":175,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":177,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4tj9d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"6DDF30E0296611EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","height":733,"id":288631,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"6of0v","text":"Thinly sliced sorghum leaf tissue.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"chopped sorghum.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i353bxfk7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i35zbxfk7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i352bxfk7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i35ybxfk7.webp","width":550}},"1":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"83FE5680296611EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","height":733,"id":288636,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"ens3c","text":"Maize B73 and sorghum BTX623 leaf tissue in enzyme solution.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"BTX623_B73_in_box.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i358bxfk7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i356bxfk7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i357bxfk7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i355bxfk7.webp","width":550}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"41mvc","text":"Incubate 4h in dark at RT w/ 40 rpm shaking.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fb7m6","text":"Add 10mL W5 solution (or volume of W5 equal to the amount of enzyme solution). Gently swirl to mix, and shake additional 1h at 80 rpm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5dj68","text":"Filter the W5 and enzyme solution mixture through 100 or 70um nylon mesh into 50 mL tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"53ebr","text":"Centrifuge @ 1000-1200 rpm 5 min to collect protoplasts to the bottom of the 50mL tube.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":87,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"5khs6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"BD25A4F0296511EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","height":733,"id":288640,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"spun_protos.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36cbxfk7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36abxfk7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36bbxfk7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i359bxfk7.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dnnnt","text":"Use a pipette to remove the supernatant and resuspend the protoplast pellet in 600 uL of suspension solution if working on sorghum, 1ml of suspension solution if working on maize.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c249b","text":"Use 9ul of resuspended protoplasts to count with a hemocytometer to determine the concentration of resuspended protoplasts.    ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":123,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":125,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"16d42","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"file","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"forceSelection":true,"guid":"D2762890296811EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","id":288070,"original_name":"B73_7_for_protocol.jpg","placeholder":"","raw_source":"","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i3kgbxfk7.jpg"}},"1":{"type":"file","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"forceSelection":true,"guid":"DB9F2110296811EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","id":288071,"original_name":"BTX623_4_for_protocol.jpg","placeholder":"","raw_source":"","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i3khbxfk7.jpg"}}}}

cases.title: Fluorescein Diacetate (FDA) viability stain
cases.description: {"blocks":[{"key":"anvs2","text":"FDA stain to check viability of protoplasts:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e3res","text":"81.2uL 1M mannitol","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eap2l","text":"43.6uL diH20","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"80k8p","text":"2.5uL FDA","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"27s6k","text":"Mix 10uL protoplast suspension with 5uL FDA stain, incubate RT 2min., load on hemocytometer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1c8h9","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":1,"key":0}],"data":{}},{"key":"6caus","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"nc92","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"DDF66210296911EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","id":288073,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i3kjbxfk7.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i3kkbxfk7.jpg","original_name":"BTX_FDA_stained_protoplasts.jpg","mime":"image/jpeg","shadow":false,"is_video":false,"width":550,"height":550,"legend":{"blocks":[{"key":"2acp","text":"Sorghum BTX623 protoplasts FDA stained","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}},"nestedSelector":null}}}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"lkl2","text":"Add more suspension solution to reduce protoplast concentration to ~2-4 x 105 cells/mL for transfection.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":76,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"98g0i","text":"In a 1.5mL tube add 20-40ug plasmid DNA and 200uL of protoplast suspension, let sit RT 5 min. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ndav","text":"Add 220uL PEG solution and mix immediately by gentle tube inversion, incubate 15 min. @ 28C.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5q4sk","text":"Quickly add 800 uL W5 solution to dilute the PEG, gently invert the tube 2x.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7gnic","text":"Collect the protoplasts by centrifuge 3min. @ 1000rpm, remove PEG and W5 supernatant. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"etot0","text":"Suspend collected protoplasts in 1mL incubation buffer and incubate in the dark @ 28C overnight with gentle ~20rpm shaking. 1.5mL tubes should be laid on their side for overnight incubation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4j3ji","text":"Centrifuge transformed protoplasts after overnight incubation @ 1000rpm for 3minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4te6f","text":"Remove the incubation buffer supernatant, resuspend the protoplast pellet in 100uL MMM and 100uL Alg-A solution. Mix by gently flicking the 1.5mL tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2k4g7","text":"Pipette a large droplet of the protoplast solution onto Poly-L-lysine coated slide well (we use 8 well chamber, 50uL protoplast droplet in each well)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4621b","text":"Allow the alginate droplet to sit for 10-15 minutes at RT for the protoplasts to settle to the surface of the glass slide.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"389sm","text":"Gently pipette 0.5-1uL droplets of W5 solution to the surface of the protoplast-alginate droplet so that the entire surface of the droplet gets coated in W5, but the protoplasts settled against the glass remain undisturbed as possible.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":236,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4vru","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"1F570090296311EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","height":261,"id":288644,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"f8eg1","text":"First solidify the outer edges of the protoplast-alginate droplet with microdroplets of W5, then work inward.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"Screen Shot 2022-08-31 at 12.27.50 PM.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36gbxfk7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36ebxfk7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36fbxfk7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36dbxfk7.webp","width":304}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f9905","text":"Allow the W5 coated protoplast-alginate droplet to sit 15 minutes RT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fnai3","text":"Pipette the equivalent volume of W5 as the volume of the protoplast-alginate droplet into the slide well containing the droplet (50uL W5: 50uL protoplast-alginate) and allow it to incubate for 45 minutes. Note: while pipetting, depress the W5 into the well very slowly and gently.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bgpcq","text":"Remove W5 and incubate the droplet in FPCN (350uL FPCN if protoplast droplet is 50uL) for 15 minutes. This is wash 1.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"djlai","text":"Remove FPCN and replace with another addition of fresh FPCN, incubate 15 minutes. This is wash 2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ha95","text":"Remove FPCN and incubate with the final FPCN or treatment solution. The alginate-embedded protoplasts are ready to be imaged.    ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":125,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":127,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ehmmf","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"D797F810296511EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","height":733,"id":288648,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"dfmk2","text":"Maize and sorghum solid protoplast-alginate droplets in FPCN solution on 8 well slide.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"8_well_FPCN.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36kbxfk7.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36ibxfk7.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36jbxfk7.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i36hbxfk7.webp","width":550}},"1":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"0D740030297211EDAADA71F4AE5F7C55","height":414,"id":288086,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"595mr","text":"24hour time-course of maize protoplasts transformed with a fluorescent construct.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/gif","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"after_GA_B2 Region1_Merged.gif","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i3kzbxfk7.gif","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i3kybxfk7.gif","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"17esd","text":"In a sterile hood, coat the bottom surface of the slide-well the protoplasts will be sitting in with 50ug/mL Poly-L-lysine, allow to sit for 30min-1hour, remove the poly-L-lysine, and allow the well-plate to air-dry. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bepub","text":"Prepare enzyme solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ba0td","text":"Prepare W5 solution, suspension solution, PEG solution, and incubation solution. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3hp7n","text":"Ensure MMM, Alg-A, and FPCN solutions are prepared for Day 2. The MMM and Alg-A solutions may be stored at 4C for 6 months or longer, FPCN may be stored at 20C for 6 months or longer. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
